{"article_id":"cUdYr1gwHBYairQa","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Hillary Clinton 's attorney David Kendall has handed over thumb drives","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"containing copies of roughly 30,000 e-mails","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"sent to and from Ms. Clinton ' s personal e-mail addresses via her private server","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to the FBI .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"The former secretary of State has also directed her staffers to release her server to federal investigators .","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"Ms. Clinton has drawn criticism","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"for using a private server and personal e-mail","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"to conduct government business during her tenure at the helm of the State Department .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"She has maintained","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"that she never sent or stored any classified information on her personal server and account .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"However , since news","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"that she had not been using a government-protected server","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"broke in March ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"at least two e-mails have been deemed `` Top Secret , Sensitive Compartmented Information ''","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"- one of the government 's highest classifications .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"Top Republicans have pointed to the retroactive designation of those e-mails as classified as evidence","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that Clinton lied about not sending classified information over her personal server .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"`` Secretary Clinton 's previous statements","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"that she possessed no classified information","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"were patently untrue , ''","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"( R )","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"of Ohio said in a statement","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"after the Clinton camp announced","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"that it would hand over the data .","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"`` Her mishandling of classified information must be fully investigated . ''","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Federal investigators are now searching for security breaches in Clinton ' s personal e-mail setup amid speculation","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"that other classified information may have been sent through the server .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"There has been no evidence","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"that Clinton encrypted the account","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"to prevent prying eyes from accessing the e-mails or her personal system .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"Clinton has `` pledged to cooperate with the government 's security inquiry ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"and","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"if there are more questions ,","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"we will continue to address them , ''","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"campaign spokesman Nick Merrill said Tuesday .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"The decision","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"to give up the server","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"came after","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"the FBI said","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Mr. Kendall was not permitted to possess classified information","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"contained in some of the e-mails ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"said a US official","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"who was not authorized to speak publicly .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Clinton 's attorney had already supplied the 30,000 e-mails","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"contained on the thumb drives","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"to investigators in December ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"but had retained copies of them on the thumb drives .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"In March , Clinton said","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"she exchanged nearly 60,000 e-mails during her four years in the Obama administration ,","depth":5},{"id":50,"text":"half of which were personal","depth":5},{"id":51,"text":"and had been discarded .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"For months after The New York Times uncovered Clinton ' s home-brew e-mail server ,","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"the Democratic candidate refused to hand it in .","depth":5},{"id":54,"text":"She claimed","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"she used it out of convenience","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"to limit the amount of electronic devices","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"she had to carry .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"you care about","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"While her use of a personal e-mail account and server did not break the rules at the time ,","depth":4},{"id":64,"text":"no other secretary of State has exclusively done so .","depth":4},{"id":65,"text":"Material from the Associated Press was used in this report .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":131,"left":123,"right":130,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":113,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":113,"left":91,"right":112,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":91,"left":70,"right":90,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":69,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":69,"left":68,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":68,"left":0,"right":67,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":67,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":72,"right":89,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":72,"left":5,"right":71,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":71,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":73,"right":88,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":73,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":79,"right":87